<subSubSection pageId="6" pageNumber="427" type="distribution">
<paragraph blockId="6.[151,1436,785,1027]" pageId="6" pageNumber="427">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,632,857,883]" pageId="6" pageNumber="427">Distribution and published records.</emphasis>
The species was described from 
<collectingCountry box="[1016,1084,857,883]" name="Iran" pageId="6" pageNumber="427">Persia</collectingCountry>
(
<collectingCountry box="[1102,1150,857,883]" name="Iran" pageId="6" pageNumber="427">Iran</collectingCountry>
) (
<bibRefCitation author="Svihla, V." box="[1175,1321,857,886]" pageId="6" pageNumber="427" pagination="107 - 132" refId="ref6781" refString="Svihla, V. (1983) Results of the Czechoslovak-Iranian entomological expeditions to Iran 1970, 1973, and 1977. Coleoptera, Oedemeridae. Acta Entomologica Musei Nationalis Pragae, 41, 107 - 132." type="journal article" year="1983">Švihla, 1983</bibRefCitation>
) and then reported for 
<collectingCountry box="[292,340,894,920]" name="Iraq" pageId="6" pageNumber="427">Iraq</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[352,400,894,920]" name="Iran" pageId="6" pageNumber="427">Iran</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[411,560,893,919]" name="Saudi Arabia" pageId="6" pageNumber="427">Saudi Arabia</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[571,817,893,919]" name="United Arab Emirates" pageId="6" pageNumber="427">United Arab Emirates</collectingCountry>
and 
<collectingCountry box="[872,954,893,919]" name="Kuwait" pageId="6" pageNumber="427">Kuwait</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Svihla, V." box="[970,1116,893,922]" pageId="6" pageNumber="427" pagination="107 - 132" refId="ref6781" refString="Svihla, V. (1983) Results of the Czechoslovak-Iranian entomological expeditions to Iran 1970, 1973, and 1977. Coleoptera, Oedemeridae. Acta Entomologica Musei Nationalis Pragae, 41, 107 - 132." type="journal article" year="1983">Švihla, 1983</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Svihla, V." box="[1128,1187,893,919]" pageId="6" pageNumber="427" pagination="260 - 266" refId="ref6819" refString="Svihla, V. (1984) Insects of Saudi Arabia. Coleoptera: Fam. Oedemeridae (part 2). Fauna of Saudi Arabia, 6, 260 - 266." type="journal article" year="1984">1984</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Kubisz, D. &amp; Iwan, D." box="[1199,1354,893,919]" pageId="6" pageNumber="427" pagination="476 - 499" refId="ref6435" refString="Kubisz, D. &amp; Iwan, D. (2020) Family Oedemeridae. In: Iwan, D. &amp; Lobl, I. (Eds.), Catalogue of Palaearctic Coleoptera. Vol. 5. 2 nd Edition. Apollo Books, Stenstrup, pp. 476 - 499." type="book chapter" year="2020">Kubisz, 2020</bibRefCitation>
). News species for the fauna of 
<collectingCountry box="[419,491,929,955]" name="Oman" pageId="6" pageNumber="427">Oman</collectingCountry>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="6.[151,1436,785,1027]" pageId="6" pageNumber="427">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,273,965,991]" pageId="6" pageNumber="427">Notes.</emphasis>
The biotope where the specimens were found is quite peculiar, being a sandy beach with mangrove trees (
<figureCitation box="[159,242,1001,1027]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="6.[151,250,1957,1981]" captionTargetBox="[212,1375,1051,1933]" captionTargetId="figure-251@6.[212,1375,1051,1933]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURE 4. Example of habitats for Oedemeridae in Oman. 4a: Wahiba sandy dunes (Alloxantha talhouki); 4b: Al Rajmi (Nacerdochroa carinatopyga, Alloxantha flava); 4c: Shinas (Probosca (Proboxantha) fuscipennis); 4d: Wadi Damm (N. carinatopyga, A. flava)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6810438" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6810438/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="427">Fig. 4c</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
